{"session_id":"svc-1778574647014241607","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-12T08:30:49.069202713Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"codex","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-9063101c-20260512T083041-fc6e29e0","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children once more; third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260512T083041-fc6e29e0/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a success. Do not mix implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260512T083041-fc6e29e0/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260512T083041-fc6e29e0/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;To request orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260512T083041-fc6e29e0/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260512T083041-fc6e29e0/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-9063101c\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003etests: replace NewCommandFactory(\u0026#34;/tmp\u0026#34;) placeholders with t.TempDir()\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;  Multiple tests in cli/cmd/ pass the literal \u0026#34;/tmp\u0026#34; as the working-directory\u0026#xA;  argument to NewCommandFactory(...). Today these tests don\u0026#39;t write files at\u0026#xA;  that path, but a future change to NewCommandFactory or its commands could\u0026#xA;  silently start writing into /tmp without any cleanup. Discovered by the\u0026#xA;  2026-05-09 test-cleanup audit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;  Hardcoded \u0026#34;/tmp\u0026#34; appears in NewCommandFactory calls in (at minimum):\u0026#xA;    - cli/cmd/version_acceptance_test.go:15\u0026#xA;    - cli/cmd/status_test.go:20\u0026#xA;    - cli/cmd/prompts_test.go:16\u0026#xA;    - cli/cmd/help_acceptance_test.go:15\u0026#xA;    - cli/cmd/security_test.go:19\u0026#xA;    - cli/cmd/contract_test.go:21,268,366\u0026#xA;    - cli/cmd/list_test.go:184\u0026#xA;    - cli/cmd/config_test.go:180\u0026#xA;  Each call passes \u0026#34;/tmp\u0026#34; because the tests verify CLI output (version\u0026#xA;  strings, help text, contract shapes, list output, etc.) where the\u0026#xA;  working-dir traversal is currently a no-op. There is no defensive\u0026#xA;  guarantee that this remains true.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;  - In each listed file:line, replace the literal \u0026#34;/tmp\u0026#34; with t.TempDir()\u0026#xA;    (Go\u0026#39;s stdlib testing helper, auto-registers cleanup).\u0026#xA;  - Verify no other behavior changes; the working dir is still a unique\u0026#xA;    temp path, just one that\u0026#39;s guaranteed empty and auto-cleaned.\u0026#xA;  - Add a CI/lint check: a small grep-based assertion (or a new linter\u0026#xA;    rule) that flags any future NewCommandFactory(\u0026#34;/tmp\u0026#34;) literal in\u0026#xA;    cli/cmd/*_test.go. The simplest implementation is a one-line addition\u0026#xA;    to lefthook\u0026#39;s no-debug or no-tmp pre-commit hook.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;  - Tests in cli/cmd/server_state_test.go and cli/internal/server/state_test.go\u0026#xA;    that embed /tmp/TestFooBar* paths in JSON test data (no filesystem I/O;\u0026#xA;    test-data only).\u0026#xA;  - Test files outside cli/cmd/.\u0026#xA;  - The genuine /tmp leak in cli/cmd/testutils_test.go GetTestLibraryPath\u0026#xA;    (covered by the sister bead on shared-fixture cleanup).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;INTERSECTIONS\u0026#xA;  - Sister bead: shared-fixture cleanup in testutils_test.go.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. grep -nE \u0026#39;NewCommandFactory\\(\u0026#34;/tmp\u0026#34;\\)\u0026#39; cli/cmd returns zero matches.\u0026#xA;2. The listed test files (version_acceptance_test.go, status_test.go, prompts_test.go, help_acceptance_test.go, security_test.go, contract_test.go, list_test.go, config_test.go) all use t.TempDir() in place of the prior \u0026#34;/tmp\u0026#34; literal.\u0026#xA;3. A pre-commit grep guard (lefthook hook or equivalent linter rule) rejects future commits containing NewCommandFactory(\u0026#34;/tmp\u0026#34;) in cli/cmd/*_test.go.\u0026#xA;4. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./cmd/... green.\u0026#xA;5. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:6, area:tests, kind:refactor, prevention\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata base-rev=\"df650b8679062993407b3be9411b8c018b14a8d1\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260512T083041-fc6e29e0\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260512T083041-fc6e29e0","base_rev":"df650b8679062993407b3be9411b8c018b14a8d1","bead_id":"ddx-9063101c","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260512T083041-fc6e29e0","correlation_id":"ddx-9063101c:20260512T083041-fc6e29e0","p